text: Phymorhynchus agina is an extinct species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Raphitomidae. ==Description== ==Distribution== This marine species has been found in Pliocene strata of Charco Azul, Panama ==References== * Olsson, Axel Adolf. "Tertiary and Quaternary fossils from the Burica Peninsula of Panama and Costa Rica." (1942): 153–258. agina Category:Gastropods described in 1942
title: Phymorhynchus agina
